{
  "local_port": 51706,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure to check your PF balance?",
  "response": "To check your Provident Fund (PF) balance, you can follow these steps:\n\n### Method 1: EPFO Portal\n\n1. **Visit the EPFO Website:**\n   - Go to the official Employee Provident Fund Organization (EPFO) website: [https://www.epfindia.gov.in](https://www.epfindia.gov.in).\n\n2. **Login to Member Portal:**\n   - Click on the 'For Employees' section under 'Our Services'.\n   - Then click on 'Member Passbook' under 'Services'.\n   - You will be redirected to the Member Passbook login page.\n\n3. **Enter Credentials:**\n   - Log in using your Universal Account Number (UAN) and password.\n   - If you haven't activated your UAN, you will need to do so first by clicking on 'Activate UAN' on the same page and following the instructions.\n\n4. **View Passbook:**\n   - Once logged in, you can view your PF passbook, which will contain details of your PF balance.\n\n### Method 2: UMANG App\n\n1. **Download UMANG App:**\n   - Download the UMANG app from Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n\n2. **Open the App:**\n   - Open the app and search for EPFO services.\n\n3. **Login:**\n   - Login using your UAN and OTP received on your registered mobile number.\n\n4. **Check PF Balance:**\n   - Go to 'Employee Centric Services' and select 'View Passbook'.\n   - You can now see your PF balance.\n\n### Method 3: SMS\n\n1. **Send SMS:**\n   - Send an SMS to 7738299899.\n   - The format of the SMS should be: EPFOHO UAN ENG.\n     - ENG stands for English. You can choose other languages by replacing 'ENG' with the first three letters of the language (e.g., HIN for Hindi).\n\n2. **Receive PF Balance:**\n   - You will receive an SMS with your PF balance details.\n\n### Method 4: Missed Call\n\n1. **Give a Missed Call:**\n   - Give a missed call to 011-22901406 from your registered mobile number.\n\n2. **Receive SMS:**\n   - You will receive an SMS with your PF balance details.\n\n### Method 5: EPFO App\n\n1. **Download EPFO App:**\n   - Download the EPFO app from Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n\n2. **Login:**\n   - Login using your UAN and OTP received on your registered mobile number.\n\n3. **Check PF Balance:**\n   - Navigate to the relevant section to check your PF balance.\n\n### Method 6: Through Employer\n\n1. **Request Statement:**\n   - You can request your employer to provide you with your PF statement.\n\n2. **Check Balance:**\n   - The employer can provide you with the latest PF balance details.\n\nBy using any of these methods, you can easily check your PF balance. Ensure that your UAN is activated and your mobile number is registered with EPFO for a smooth experience.",
